column2: Unique ID given to nest or random point.
Type of point. Nest point or random point.
For nests in the breeding season, identifies whether data was collected the date the nest was found, within the (estimated) hatch date, or after hatch.
Nest fate: hatch, fail, or unknown.
Date of sample collection.
Season of collection: summer (nesting season) or fall (after nesting season has ended).
Geographic latitude in decimal degrees. Positive values are North, negative are South. Range: -90.0 to 90.0.
Geographic longitude in decimal degrees. Positive values are East, negative are West. Range: -180.0 to 180.0
Unspecified object. Whether or not there was an object present that was unspecific to the point.
Specified object: Presence or absence of a specific object (inanimate object, vegetation, or no object) at the nest cup within 15 cm.
